{"thig1.1":{"thig1.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.1 ","html":"<article id='thig1.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.1:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.1:0.3":{"pli":"Aññatarātherīgāthā ","eng":"An Unnamed Nun (1st) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.1:1.0":{"pli":"Namo tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sammāsambuddhassa. ","eng":"Homage to him, the blessed one, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha! ","html":"<p class='namo'><a class='sc'></a>{}</p>"},"thig1.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Sukhaṃ supāhi therike, ","eng":"Sleep softly, little nun, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.1:1.2":{"pli":"Katvā coḷena pārutā; ","eng":"wrapped in the cloth you sewed yourself; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.1:1.3":{"pli":"Upasanto hi te rāgo, ","eng":"for your desire has been quelled, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.1:1.4":{"pli":"Sukkhaḍākaṃ va kumbhiyan”ti. ","eng":"like vegetables boiled dry in a pot. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.1:2.1":{"pli":"Itthaṃ sudaṃ aññatarā therī apaññātā bhikkhunī gāthaṃ abhāsitthāti. ","eng":"That is how this verse was recited by a certain unnamed nun. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.10":{"thig1.10:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.10 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.10 ","html":"<article id='thig1.10'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.10:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.10:0.3":{"pli":"Upasamātherīgāthā ","eng":"Upasamā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.10:1.1":{"pli":"“Upasame tare oghaṃ, ","eng":"Upasamā, cross the flood, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.10:1.2":{"pli":"maccudheyyaṃ suduttaraṃ; ","eng":"Death’s dominion so hard to pass. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.10:1.3":{"pli":"Dhārehi antimaṃ dehaṃ, ","eng":"When you have vanquished Māra and his mount, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.10:1.4":{"pli":"jetvā māraṃ savāhinin”ti. ","eng":"bear your final body. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.10:2.1":{"pli":"… Upasamā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.11":{"thig1.11:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.11 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.11 ","html":"<article id='thig1.11'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.11:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.11:0.3":{"pli":"Muttātherīgāthā ","eng":"Muttā (2nd) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.11:1.1":{"pli":"“Sumuttā sādhumuttāmhi, ","eng":"I’m well freed, so very well freed, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Compare with <a href='index.html?q=thig2.3'>Thig 2.3</a> and <a href='index.html?q=thag1.43'>Thag 1.43</a>. "},"thig1.11:1.2":{"pli":"tīhi khujjehi muttiyā; ","eng":"freed from the three things that humped me: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The commentary explains that the first two things make you crooked: (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>khujjakaraṇahetutāya tadubhayaṁ “khujja”nti vuttaṁ</i>), while the husband <em>is</em> crooked (a hunchback). This may be so, but I think it is a double entendre. "},"thig1.11:1.3":{"pli":"Udukkhalena musalena, ","eng":"the mortar, the pestle, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The mortar and pestle feature prominently in the sexual imagery of Rig Veda 1.29, where the kitchen implements are analogized with the pressing of soma on the altar. Both <i lang='pi' translate='no'>musala</i> and “pestle” derive from roots “to pound”. "},"thig1.11:1.4":{"pli":"patinā khujjakena ca; ","eng":"and my humpbacked husband. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.11:1.5":{"pli":"Muttāmhi jātimaraṇā, ","eng":"I’m freed from birth and death; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.11:1.6":{"pli":"bhavanetti samūhatā”ti. ","eng":"the leash to existence is eradicated. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.11:2.1":{"pli":"… Muttā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.12":{"thig1.12:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.12 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.12 ","html":"<article id='thig1.12'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.12:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.12:0.3":{"pli":"Dhammadinnātherīgāthā ","eng":"Dhammadinnā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.12:1.1":{"pli":"“Chandajātā avasāyī, ","eng":"One who is eager and determined ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.12:1.2":{"pli":"Manasā ca phuṭā siyā; ","eng":"would be filled with awareness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.12:1.3":{"pli":"Kāmesu appaṭibaddhacittā, ","eng":"Their mind not bound to pleasures of sense, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.12:1.4":{"pli":"Uddhaṃsotāti vuccatī”ti. ","eng":"they’re said to be heading upstream. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.12:2.1":{"pli":"… Dhammadinnā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.13":{"thig1.13:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.13 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.13 ","html":"<article id='thig1.13'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.13:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.13:0.3":{"pli":"Visākhātherīgāthā ","eng":"Visākhā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.13:1.1":{"pli":"“Karotha buddhasāsanaṃ, ","eng":"Do the Buddha’s bidding, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.13:1.2":{"pli":"yaṃ katvā nānutappati; ","eng":"you won’t regret it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.13:1.3":{"pli":"Khippaṃ pādāni dhovitvā, ","eng":"Having quickly washed your feet, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.13:1.4":{"pli":"ekamante nisīdathā”ti. ","eng":"sit in a discreet place to meditate. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.13:2.1":{"pli":"… Visākhā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.14":{"thig1.14:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.14 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.14 ","html":"<article id='thig1.14'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.14:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.14:0.3":{"pli":"Sumanātherīgāthā ","eng":"Sumanā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.14:1.1":{"pli":"“Dhātuyo dukkhato disvā, ","eng":"Having seen the elements as suffering, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.14:1.2":{"pli":"mā jātiṃ punarāgami; ","eng":"don’t get reborn again. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.14:1.3":{"pli":"Bhave chandaṃ virājetvā, ","eng":"When you’ve discarded desire for rebirth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.14:1.4":{"pli":"upasantā carissasī”ti. ","eng":"you will live at peace. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.14:2.1":{"pli":"… Sumanā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.15":{"thig1.15:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.15 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.15 ","html":"<article id='thig1.15'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.15:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.15:0.3":{"pli":"Uttarātherīgāthā ","eng":"Uttarā (1st) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.15:1.1":{"pli":"“Kāyena saṃvutā āsiṃ, ","eng":"I was restrained ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.15:1.2":{"pli":"vācāya uda cetasā; ","eng":"in body, speech, and mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.15:1.3":{"pli":"Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha, ","eng":"Having plucked out craving, root and all, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.15:1.4":{"pli":"sītibhūtāmhi nibbutā”ti. ","eng":"I’m cooled and quenched. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.15:2.1":{"pli":"… Uttarā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.16":{"thig1.16:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.16 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.16 ","html":"<article id='thig1.16'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.16:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.16:0.3":{"pli":"Vuḍḍhapabbajitasumanātherīgāthā ","eng":"Sumanā, Who Went Forth Late in Life ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.16:1.1":{"pli":"“Sukhaṃ tvaṃ vuḍḍhike sehi, ","eng":"Sleep softly, old lady, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.16:1.2":{"pli":"katvā coḷena pārutā; ","eng":"wrapped in the cloth you sewed yourself; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.16:1.3":{"pli":"Upasanto hi te rāgo, ","eng":"for your desire has been quelled, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.16:1.4":{"pli":"sītibhūtāsi nibbutā”ti. ","eng":"you’re cooled and quenched. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.16:2.1":{"pli":"… Sumanā vuḍḍhapabbajitā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.17":{"thig1.17:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.17 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.17 ","html":"<article id='thig1.17'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.17:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.17:0.3":{"pli":"Dhammātherīgāthā ","eng":"Dhammā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.17:1.1":{"pli":"“Piṇḍapātaṃ caritvāna, ","eng":"I wandered for alms ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.17:1.2":{"pli":"daṇḍamolubbha dubbalā; ","eng":"though feeble, leaning on a staff. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.17:1.3":{"pli":"Vedhamānehi gattehi, ","eng":"My limbs wobbled ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.17:1.4":{"pli":"tattheva nipatiṃ chamā; ","eng":"and I fell to the ground right there. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.17:1.5":{"pli":"Disvā ādīnavaṃ kāye, ","eng":"Seeing the danger of the body, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.17:1.6":{"pli":"atha cittaṃ vimucci me”ti. ","eng":"my mind was freed. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.17:2.1":{"pli":"… Dhammā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.18":{"thig1.18:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.18 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.18 ","html":"<article id='thig1.18'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.18:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.18:0.3":{"pli":"Saṅghātherīgāthā ","eng":"Saṅghā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.18:1.1":{"pli":"“Hitvā ghare pabbajitvā, ","eng":"I gave up my home, my child, my cattle, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.18:1.2":{"pli":"hitvā puttaṃ pasuṃ piyaṃ; ","eng":"and all that I love, and went forth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.18:1.3":{"pli":"Hitvā rāgañca dosañca, ","eng":"And now that I’ve given up desire and hate, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.18:1.4":{"pli":"avijjañca virājiya; ","eng":"dispelled ignorance, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.18:1.5":{"pli":"Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha, ","eng":"and plucked out craving, root and all, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.18:1.6":{"pli":"upasantāmhi nibbutā”ti. ","eng":"I’m at peace, I’m quenched. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.18:2.1":{"pli":"… Saṅghā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig1.18:3.1":{"pli":"Ekakanipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.2":{"thig1.2:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.2 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.2 ","html":"<article id='thig1.2'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.2:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.2:0.3":{"pli":"Muttātherīgāthā ","eng":"Muttā (1st) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.2:1.1":{"pli":"“Mutte muccassu yogehi, ","eng":"Muttā, be released from your yokes, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.2:1.2":{"pli":"cando rāhuggahā iva; ","eng":"like the moon released from the eclipse. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.2:1.3":{"pli":"Vippamuttena cittena, ","eng":"When your mind is released, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.2:1.4":{"pli":"anaṇā bhuñja piṇḍakan”ti. ","eng":"enjoy your alms free of debt. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.2:2.1":{"pli":"Itthaṃ sudaṃ bhagavā muttaṃ sikkhamānaṃ imāya gāthāya abhiṇhaṃ ovadatīti. ","eng":"That is how the Buddha regularly advised the trainee nun Muttā with these verses. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.3":{"thig1.3:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.3 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.3 ","html":"<article id='thig1.3'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.3:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.3:0.3":{"pli":"Puṇṇātherīgāthā ","eng":"Puṇṇā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.3:1.1":{"pli":"“Puṇṇe pūrassu dhammehi, ","eng":"Puṇṇā, be filled with good qualities, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.3:1.2":{"pli":"Cando pannaraseriva; ","eng":"like the moon on the fifteenth day. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.3:1.3":{"pli":"Paripuṇṇāya paññāya, ","eng":"When your wisdom is full, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.3:1.4":{"pli":"Tamokhandhaṃ padālayā”ti. ","eng":"shatter the mass of darkness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.3:2.1":{"pli":"Itthaṃ sudaṃ puṇṇā therī gāthaṃ abhāsitthāti. ","eng":"That is how this verse was recited by the senior nun Puṇṇā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.4":{"thig1.4:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.4 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.4 ","html":"<article id='thig1.4'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.4:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.4:0.3":{"pli":"Tissātherīgāthā ","eng":"Tissā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.4:1.1":{"pli":"“Tisse sikkhassu sikkhāya, ","eng":"Tissā, train in the trainings—","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.4:1.2":{"pli":"mā taṃ yogā upaccaguṃ; ","eng":"don’t let your yokes overcome you. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.4:1.3":{"pli":"Sabbayogavisaṃyuttā, ","eng":"Unyoked from all yokes, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.4:1.4":{"pli":"cara loke anāsavā”ti. ","eng":"live in the world free of defilements. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.4:2.1":{"pli":"… Tissā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.5":{"thig1.5:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.5 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.5 ","html":"<article id='thig1.5'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.5:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.5:0.3":{"pli":"Aññatarātissātherīgāthā ","eng":"Another Tissā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.5:1.1":{"pli":"“Tisse yuñjassu dhammehi, ","eng":"Tissā, apply yourself to good qualities—","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.5:1.2":{"pli":"khaṇo taṃ mā upaccagā; ","eng":"don’t let the moment pass you by. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.5:1.3":{"pli":"Khaṇātītā hi socanti, ","eng":"For if you miss your moment, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.5:1.4":{"pli":"nirayamhi samappitā”ti. ","eng":"you’ll grieve when sent to hell. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.5:2.1":{"pli":"… Aññatarā tissā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.6":{"thig1.6:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.6 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.6 ","html":"<article id='thig1.6'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.6:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.6:0.3":{"pli":"Dhīrātherīgāthā ","eng":"Dhīrā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.6:1.1":{"pli":"“Dhīre nirodhaṃ phusehi, ","eng":"Dhīrā, touch cessation, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.6:1.2":{"pli":"Saññāvūpasamaṃ sukhaṃ; ","eng":"the blissful settling of perception. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.6:1.3":{"pli":"Ārādhayāhi nibbānaṃ, ","eng":"Win extinguishment, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.6:1.4":{"pli":"Yogakkhemamanuttaran”ti. ","eng":"the supreme sanctuary from the yoke. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.6:2.1":{"pli":"… Dhīrā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.7":{"thig1.7:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.7 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.7 ","html":"<article id='thig1.7'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.7:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.7:0.3":{"pli":"Vīrātherīgāthā ","eng":"Vīrā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.7:1.1":{"pli":"“Vīrā vīrehi dhammehi, ","eng":"She’s known as Vīrā because of her heroic qualities, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.7:1.2":{"pli":"bhikkhunī bhāvitindriyā; ","eng":"a nun with faculties developed. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.7:1.3":{"pli":"Dhāreti antimaṃ dehaṃ, ","eng":"She bears her final body, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.7:1.4":{"pli":"jetvā māraṃ savāhinin”ti. ","eng":"having vanquished Māra with his legions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.7:2.1":{"pli":"… Vīrā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.8":{"thig1.8:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.8 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.8 ","html":"<article id='thig1.8'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.8:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.8:0.3":{"pli":"Mittātherīgāthā ","eng":"Mittā (1st) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.8:1.1":{"pli":"“Saddhāya pabbajitvāna, ","eng":"Having gone forth in faith, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.8:1.2":{"pli":"mitte mittaratā bhava; ","eng":"appreciate your spiritual friends, Mittā. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.8:1.3":{"pli":"Bhāvehi kusale dhamme, ","eng":"Develop skillful qualities ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.8:1.4":{"pli":"yogakkhemassa pattiyā”ti. ","eng":"for the sake of sanctuary from the yoke. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.8:2.1":{"pli":"… Mittā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig1.9":{"thig1.9:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 1.9 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 1.9 ","html":"<article id='thig1.9'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig1.9:0.2":{"pli":"Ekakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Ones ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig1.9:0.3":{"pli":"Bhadrātherīgāthā ","eng":"Bhadrā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig1.9:1.1":{"pli":"“Saddhāya pabbajitvāna, ","eng":"Having gone forth in faith, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.9:1.2":{"pli":"bhadre bhadraratā bhava; ","eng":"appreciate your blessings, Bhadrā. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.9:1.3":{"pli":"Bhāvehi kusale dhamme, ","eng":"Develop skillful qualities ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig1.9:1.4":{"pli":"yogakkhemamanuttaran”ti. ","eng":"for the sake of the supreme sanctuary from the yoke. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig1.9:2.1":{"pli":"… Bhadrā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig10.1":{"thig10.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 10.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 10.1 ","html":"<article id='thig10.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig10.1:0.2":{"pli":"Ekādasakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Elevens ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig10.1:0.3":{"pli":"Kisāgotamītherīgāthā ","eng":"Kisāgotamī ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig10.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Kalyāṇamittatā muninā, ","eng":"“Pointing out how the world works, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:1.2":{"pli":"lokaṃ ādissa vaṇṇitā; ","eng":"the sages have praised good friendship. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:1.3":{"pli":"Kalyāṇamitte bhajamāno, ","eng":"Associating with good friends, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:1.4":{"pli":"api bālo paṇḍito assa. ","eng":"even a fool becomes astute. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:2.1":{"pli":"Bhajitabbā sappurisā, ","eng":"Associate with true persons, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:2.2":{"pli":"Paññā tathā vaḍḍhati bhajantānaṃ; ","eng":"for that is how wisdom grows. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:2.3":{"pli":"Bhajamāno sappurise, ","eng":"Should you associate with true persons, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:2.4":{"pli":"Sabbehipi dukkhehi pamucceyya. ","eng":"you would be freed from all suffering. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:3.1":{"pli":"Dukkhañca vijāneyya, ","eng":"And you would understand suffering, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:3.2":{"pli":"Dukkhassa ca samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ; ","eng":"its origin and cessation, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:3.3":{"pli":"Aṭṭhaṅgikañca maggaṃ, ","eng":"the eightfold path, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:3.4":{"pli":"Cattāripi ariyasaccāni”. ","eng":"and so the four noble truths.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:4.1":{"pli":"“Dukkho itthibhāvo, ","eng":"“‘A woman’s life is painful,’ ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:4.2":{"pli":"Akkhāto purisadammasārathinā; ","eng":"explained the Buddha, <j>guide for those who wish to train, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Here, it seems, Kisāgotamī is quoting or paraphrasing the Buddha. "},"thig10.1:4.3":{"pli":"Sapattikampi hi dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"‘and for a co-wife it’s especially so. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:4.4":{"pli":"Appekaccā sakiṃ vijātāyo. ","eng":"After giving birth just once, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:5.1":{"pli":"Galake api kantanti, ","eng":"some women even cut their own throat, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:5.2":{"pli":"Sukhumāliniyo visāni khādanti; ","eng":"while delicate ladies take poison. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:5.3":{"pli":"Janamārakamajjhagatā, ","eng":"Being guilty of killing a person, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Read <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jana-māraka’m’ajjhagatā</i>. "},"thig10.1:5.4":{"pli":"Ubhopi byasanāni anubhonti”. ","eng":"they both undergo ruin.’” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Ubho</i> here refers to “both” kinds of women who kill themselves. It seems the verse is about post-partum depression. "},"thig10.1:6.1":{"pli":"“Upavijaññā gacchantī, ","eng":"“I was on the road, near to giving birth, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:6.2":{"pli":"addasāhaṃ patiṃ mataṃ; ","eng":"when I saw my husband dead. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:6.3":{"pli":"Panthamhi vijāyitvāna, ","eng":"I gave birth there on the road ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:6.4":{"pli":"appattāva sakaṃ gharaṃ. ","eng":"before I’d reached my own house. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:7.1":{"pli":"Dve puttā kālakatā, ","eng":"My two children have died, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:7.2":{"pli":"Patī ca panthe mato kapaṇikāya; ","eng":"and on the road my husband lies dead—<j>oh woe is me! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:7.3":{"pli":"Mātā pitā ca bhātā, ","eng":"Mother, father, and brother ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:7.4":{"pli":"Ḍayhanti ca ekacitakāyaṃ”. ","eng":"all burning up on the same pyre.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:8.1":{"pli":"“Khīṇakulīne kapaṇe, ","eng":"“Oh woe is you whose family is lost, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:8.2":{"pli":"Anubhūtaṃ te dukhaṃ aparimāṇaṃ; ","eng":"the suffering you have undergone has no measure; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:8.3":{"pli":"Assū ca te pavattaṃ, ","eng":"you have been shedding tears ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:8.4":{"pli":"Bahūni ca jātisahassāni. ","eng":"for many thousands of lives.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:9.1":{"pli":"Vasitā susānamajjhe, ","eng":"“While staying in the charnel ground, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:9.2":{"pli":"Athopi khāditāni puttamaṃsāni; ","eng":"I saw my son’s flesh being eaten. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:9.3":{"pli":"Hatakulikā sabbagarahitā, ","eng":"With my family destroyed, condemned by all, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:9.4":{"pli":"Matapatikā amatamadhigacchiṃ. ","eng":"and my husband dead, I realized freedom from death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:10.1":{"pli":"Bhāvito me maggo, ","eng":"I’ve developed the noble eightfold path ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:10.2":{"pli":"Ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko amatagāmī; ","eng":"leading to freedom from death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:10.3":{"pli":"Nibbānaṃ sacchikataṃ, ","eng":"I’ve realized extinguishment, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:10.4":{"pli":"Dhammādāsaṃ avekkhiṃhaṃ. ","eng":"as seen in the mirror of the Dhamma. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig10.1:11.1":{"pli":"Ahamamhi kantasallā, ","eng":"I’ve plucked out the dart, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:11.2":{"pli":"Ohitabhārā katañhi karaṇīyaṃ; ","eng":"laid down the burden, <j>and done what needed to be done.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:11.3":{"pli":"Kisā gotamī therī, ","eng":"The senior nun Kisāgotamī, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig10.1:11.4":{"pli":"Vimuttacittā imaṃ bhaṇī”ti. ","eng":"her mind released, said this. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig10.1:12.1":{"pli":"… Kisā gotamī therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig10.1:13.1":{"pli":"Ekādasakanipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig11.1":{"thig11.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 11.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 11.1 ","html":"<article id='thig11.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig11.1:0.2":{"pli":"Dvādasakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twelves ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig11.1:0.3":{"pli":"Uppalavaṇṇātherīgāthā ","eng":"Uppalavaṇṇā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig11.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Ubho mātā ca dhītā ca, ","eng":"“The two of us were co-wives, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:1.2":{"pli":"mayaṃ āsuṃ sapattiyo; ","eng":"though we were mother and daughter. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:1.3":{"pli":"Tassā me ahu saṃvego, ","eng":"I was struck with a sense of urgency, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:1.4":{"pli":"abbhuto lomahaṃsano. ","eng":"so astonishing and hair-raising! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:2.1":{"pli":"Dhiratthu kāmā asucī, ","eng":"Curse those filthy sensual pleasures, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:2.2":{"pli":"duggandhā bahukaṇṭakā; ","eng":"so nasty and thorny, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:2.3":{"pli":"Yattha mātā ca dhītā ca, ","eng":"where we, both mother and daughter, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:2.4":{"pli":"sabhariyā mayaṃ ahuṃ. ","eng":"had to be co-wives together. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:3.1":{"pli":"Kāmesvādīnavaṃ disvā, ","eng":"Seeing the danger in sensual pleasures, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:3.2":{"pli":"nekkhammaṃ daṭṭhu khemato; ","eng":"seeing renunciation as sanctuary, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:3.3":{"pli":"Sā pabbajjiṃ rājagahe, ","eng":"I went forth in Rājagaha ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:3.4":{"pli":"agārasmānagāriyaṃ. ","eng":"from the lay life to homelessness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:4.1":{"pli":"Pubbenivāsaṃ jānāmi, ","eng":"I know my past lives; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:4.2":{"pli":"dibbacakkhu visodhitaṃ; ","eng":"my clairvoyance is clarified; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:4.3":{"pli":"Cetopariccañāṇañca, ","eng":"I encompass the minds of others; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:4.4":{"pli":"sotadhātu visodhitā. ","eng":"my clairaudience is purified; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:5.1":{"pli":"Iddhīpi me sacchikatā, ","eng":"I’ve realized the psychic powers, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:5.2":{"pli":"patto me āsavakkhayo; ","eng":"and attained the ending of defilements. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:5.3":{"pli":"Chaḷabhiññā sacchikatā, ","eng":"I’ve realized the six kinds of direct knowledge, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:5.4":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanaṃ. ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:6.1":{"pli":"Iddhiyā abhinimmitvā, ","eng":"I created a four-horsed chariot ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:6.2":{"pli":"caturassaṃ rathaṃ ahaṃ; ","eng":"using my psychic powers. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:6.3":{"pli":"Buddhassa pāde vanditvā, ","eng":"Then I bowed at the feet of the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:6.4":{"pli":"lokanāthassa tādino”. ","eng":"the glorious protector of the world.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:7.1":{"pli":"“Supupphitaggaṃ upagamma pādapaṃ, ","eng":"“You’ve come to this sal tree all crowned with flowers, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:7.2":{"pli":"Ekā tuvaṃ tiṭṭhasi sālamūle; ","eng":"and stand at its root all alone. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:7.3":{"pli":"Na cāpi te dutiyo atthi koci, ","eng":"But you have no male companion with you— ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The parallel verse at <a href='index.html?q=sn5.5#2.3'>SN 5.5:2.3</a> has, “There is no-one to whom you are second in the element of beauty” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>na catthi te dutiyā vaṇṇadhātu,</i>). The two lines use <i lang='pi' translate='no'>dutiya</i> (“second”) in different senses, as the ordinal number, and as “companion”. The Therīgāthā commentary offers two explanations, the second of which appears to lean on a version of the line similar to that found in SN 5.5. This, together with the fact that the unusual term <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vaṇṇadhātu</i> in that line seems like a direct reference to her name, suggests that the SN version may be the original one. "},"thig11.1:7.4":{"pli":"Bāle na tvaṃ bhāyasi dhuttakānaṃ”. ","eng":"silly girl, aren’t you afraid of rascals?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:8.1":{"pli":"“Sataṃ sahassānipi dhuttakānaṃ, ","eng":"“Even if 100,000 rascals like this ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:8.2":{"pli":"Samāgatā edisakā bhaveyyuṃ; ","eng":"were to gang up, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:8.3":{"pli":"Lomaṃ na iñje napi sampavedhe, ","eng":"I’d stir not a hair nor tremble. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:8.4":{"pli":"Kiṃ me tuvaṃ māra karissaseko. ","eng":"What could you do to me all alone, Māra? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:9.1":{"pli":"Esā antaradhāyāmi, ","eng":"I’ll vanish, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:9.2":{"pli":"kucchiṃ vā pavisāmi te; ","eng":"or I’ll enter your belly; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:9.3":{"pli":"Bhamukantare tiṭṭhāmi, ","eng":"I could stand between your eyebrows ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:9.4":{"pli":"tiṭṭhantiṃ maṃ na dakkhasi. ","eng":"and you still wouldn’t see me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:10.1":{"pli":"Cittamhi vasībhūtāhaṃ, ","eng":"I’m the master of my own mind, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:10.2":{"pli":"iddhipādā subhāvitā; ","eng":"I’ve developed the bases of psychic power well. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:10.3":{"pli":"Chaḷabhiññā sacchikatā, ","eng":"I’ve realized the six kinds of direct knowledge, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:10.4":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanaṃ. ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:11.1":{"pli":"Sattisūlūpamā kāmā, ","eng":"Sensual pleasures are like swords and spears; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:11.2":{"pli":"khandhāsaṃ adhikuṭṭanā; ","eng":"the aggregates are their chopping block. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:11.3":{"pli":"Yaṃ tvaṃ ‘kāmaratiṃ’ brūsi, ","eng":"What you call erotic delight ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:11.4":{"pli":"‘āratī’ dāni sā mama. ","eng":"is now no delight for me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig11.1:12.1":{"pli":"Sabbattha vihatā nandī, ","eng":"Relishing is banished in every respect, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:12.2":{"pli":"Tamokhandho padālito; ","eng":"and the mass of darkness is shattered. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:12.3":{"pli":"Evaṃ jānāhi pāpima, ","eng":"So know this, Wicked One: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig11.1:12.4":{"pli":"Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti. ","eng":"you’re beaten, terminator!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig11.1:13.1":{"pli":"… Uppalavaṇṇā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig11.1:14.1":{"pli":"Dvādasakanipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}},"thig12.1":{"thig12.1:0.1":{"pli":"Therīgāthā 12.1 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Nuns 12.1 ","html":"<article id='thig12.1'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thig12.1:0.2":{"pli":"Soḷasakanipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Sixteens ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thig12.1:0.3":{"pli":"Puṇṇātherīgāthā ","eng":"Puṇṇikā ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thig12.1:1.1":{"pli":"“Udahārī ahaṃ sīte, ","eng":"“I used to be a water-carrier. Even when it was cold, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:1.2":{"pli":"sadā udakamotariṃ; ","eng":"I would always plunge into the water, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Norman and Ṭhānissaro, evidently under the influence of the commentary, translate in present tense, but <i lang='pi' translate='no'>udakamotariṁ</i> is an aorist in past tense, as is rendered by Mahendra. If the commentary is correct, she is telling a story from before she ordained. But both the brahmin’s respectful form of addresses (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>bhoti</i>) and the boldness of her teachings suggest she was already a nun. "},"thig12.1:1.3":{"pli":"Ayyānaṃ daṇḍabhayabhītā, ","eng":"afraid of my masters’ beatings, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Ayyānaṁ</i> is ambiguous; it could be either male or female. "},"thig12.1:1.4":{"pli":"vācādosabhayaṭṭitā. ","eng":"harassed by fear of abuse and anger. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:2.1":{"pli":"Kassa brāhmaṇa tvaṃ bhīto, ","eng":"Brahmin, what are you afraid of, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:2.2":{"pli":"sadā udakamotari; ","eng":"that you always plunge into the water, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:2.3":{"pli":"Vedhamānehi gattehi, ","eng":"your limbs trembling ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:2.4":{"pli":"sītaṃ vedayase bhusaṃ”. ","eng":"in the freezing cold?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:3.1":{"pli":"“Jānantī vata maṃ bhoti, ","eng":"“Oh, but you already know, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:3.2":{"pli":"puṇṇike paripucchasi; ","eng":"Madam Puṇṇikā, when you ask me: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:3.3":{"pli":"Karontaṃ kusalaṃ kammaṃ, ","eng":"I am doing good deeds, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:3.4":{"pli":"rundhantaṃ katapāpakaṃ. ","eng":"to ward off the wickedness I have done. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:4.1":{"pli":"Yo ca vuḍḍho daharo vā, ","eng":"Whosoever young or old ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:4.2":{"pli":"pāpakammaṃ pakubbati; ","eng":"performs a wicked deed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:4.3":{"pli":"Dakābhisecanā sopi, ","eng":"by ablution in water they are ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:4.4":{"pli":"pāpakammā pamuccati”. ","eng":"released from their wicked deed.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:5.1":{"pli":"“Ko nu te idamakkhāsi, ","eng":"“Who on earth told you this, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:5.2":{"pli":"ajānantassa ajānako; ","eng":"one ignoramus to another: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:5.3":{"pli":"Dakābhisecanā nāma, ","eng":"‘Actually, by ablution in water one is ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:5.4":{"pli":"pāpakammā pamuccati. ","eng":"released from a wicked deed.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:6.1":{"pli":"Saggaṃ nūna gamissanti, ","eng":"Would not they all go to heaven, then: ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:6.2":{"pli":"sabbe maṇḍūkakacchapā; ","eng":"all the frogs and the turtles, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:6.3":{"pli":"Nāgā ca susumārā ca, ","eng":"dragons, dolphins, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Here, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>nāga</i> cannot be cobra or elephant, so it must be the supernatural creature, which is said to live in underwater lairs. | <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Susumāra</i> (literally “child-killer”) may be either the Gangetic dolphin (<a href='index.html?q=mn129#21.3'>MN 129:21.3</a>) or the crocodile (<a href='index.html?q=cp27#1.3'>Cp 27:1.3</a>). The dolphin is more obviously a “water-dweller”. "},"thig12.1:6.4":{"pli":"ye caññe udake carā. ","eng":"and other water-dwellers too? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:7.1":{"pli":"Orabbhikā sūkarikā, ","eng":"Butchers of sheep and pigs, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:7.2":{"pli":"macchikā migabandhakā; ","eng":"fishermen, animal trappers, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:7.3":{"pli":"Corā ca vajjhaghātā ca, ","eng":"bandits, executioners, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:7.4":{"pli":"ye caññe pāpakammino; ","eng":"and others of evil deeds: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:7.5":{"pli":"Dakābhisecanā tepi, ","eng":"by ablution in water they too would be ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:7.6":{"pli":"pāpakammā pamuccare. ","eng":"released from their wicked deeds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:8.1":{"pli":"Sace imā nadiyo te, ","eng":"If these rivers had carried away ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:8.2":{"pli":"pāpaṃ pubbe kataṃ vahuṃ; ","eng":"your bad deeds in the past, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:8.3":{"pli":"Puññampimā vaheyyuṃ te, ","eng":"they would also carry away your good deeds, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:8.4":{"pli":"tena tvaṃ paribāhiro. ","eng":"from which you’d be prevented. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:9.1":{"pli":"Yassa brāhmaṇa tvaṃ bhīto, ","eng":"Brahmin, the thing that you are afraid of, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:9.2":{"pli":"sadā udakamotari; ","eng":"when you always plunge into the water, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:9.3":{"pli":"Tameva brahme mā kāsi, ","eng":"do not do that very thing, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:9.4":{"pli":"mā te sītaṃ chaviṃ hane”. ","eng":"don’t let the cold harm your skin.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:10.1":{"pli":"“Kummaggapaṭipannaṃ maṃ, ","eng":"“I have been on the wrong path, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:10.2":{"pli":"ariyamaggaṃ samānayi; ","eng":"and you’ve guided me to the noble path. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:10.3":{"pli":"Dakābhisecanā bhoti, ","eng":"Madam, I give to you ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:10.4":{"pli":"imaṃ sāṭaṃ dadāmi te”. ","eng":"this ablution cloth.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:11.1":{"pli":"“Tuyheva sāṭako hotu, ","eng":"“Keep the cloth for yourself, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:11.2":{"pli":"nāhamicchāmi sāṭakaṃ; ","eng":"I do not want it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:11.3":{"pli":"Sace bhāyasi dukkhassa, ","eng":"If you fear suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:11.4":{"pli":"sace te dukkhamappiyaṃ. ","eng":"if you don’t like suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:12.1":{"pli":"Mākāsi pāpakaṃ kammaṃ, ","eng":"then don’t do bad deeds ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:12.2":{"pli":"āvi vā yadi vā raho; ","eng":"either openly or in secret. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:12.3":{"pli":"Sace ca pāpakaṃ kammaṃ, ","eng":"If you should do a bad deed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:12.4":{"pli":"karissasi karosi vā. ","eng":"or you’re doing one now, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:13.1":{"pli":"Na te dukkhā pamutyatthi, ","eng":"you won’t be freed from suffering, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:13.2":{"pli":"upeccāpi palāyato; ","eng":"though you fly away and flee. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:13.3":{"pli":"Sace bhāyasi dukkhassa, ","eng":"If you fear suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:13.4":{"pli":"sace te dukkhamappiyaṃ. ","eng":"if you don’t like suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:14.1":{"pli":"Upehi saraṇaṃ buddhaṃ, ","eng":"go for refuge to the Buddha, the unaffected, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:14.2":{"pli":"dhammaṃ saṅghañca tādinaṃ; ","eng":"to his teaching and to the Sangha. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:14.3":{"pli":"Samādiyāhi sīlāni, ","eng":"Undertake the precepts, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:14.4":{"pli":"taṃ te atthāya hehiti”. ","eng":"that will be good for you.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:15.1":{"pli":"“Upemi saraṇaṃ buddhaṃ, ","eng":"“I go for refuge to the Buddha, the unaffected, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:15.2":{"pli":"dhammaṃ saṅghañca tādinaṃ; ","eng":"to his teaching and to the Sangha. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:15.3":{"pli":"Samādiyāmi sīlāni, ","eng":"I undertake the precepts, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:15.4":{"pli":"taṃ me atthāya hehiti. ","eng":"that will be good for me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thig12.1:16.1":{"pli":"Brahmabandhu pure āsiṃ, ","eng":"I used to be brahmin only by kin, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:16.2":{"pli":"ajjamhi saccabrāhmaṇo; ","eng":"today I truly am a brahmin! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:16.3":{"pli":"Tevijjo vedasampanno, ","eng":"Master of the three knowledges, <j>accomplished in wisdom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thig12.1:16.4":{"pli":"sottiyo camhi nhātako”ti. ","eng":"I’m a scholar, a bathed initiate.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thig12.1:17.1":{"pli":"… Puṇṇā therī …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p>"},"thig12.1:18.1":{"pli":"Soḷasakanipāto niṭṭhito. ","html":"<p class='endbook'>{}</p></article>"}}}